26/07/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The agreement establishing a new centre-right formation, composed of the National Liberal Party, Popular Action and National Peasant Christian Democratic Party (PNTCD), will be signed next week in Timisoara, according to an announcement Wednesday (July 25th). 
Marius Popovici, president of the Timis branch of PNTCD, said the protocol document would cover positions in upcoming elections for members of the European Parliament (EP), as well as local and parliamentary elections due next year. 
The new alliance wants to promote social and economic integration and a stronger EP representation. 
(Mediafax - 25/07/07)
